places.name: 雪可屋

plus_code.compound_code: 2G9J+RX 大學里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Alley 3, Lane 74, Wenzhou St, 2號1樓

reviews.text:
Great vibe and fresh look after the relocation. Great drip coffee offered, lots of choices to choose from. The shop also offers good quality in-house roasted coffee beans at reasonable prices. The biggest surprise of all is menu, from beverages that you get from tea shop such as bubble tea and smoothies to the variety of snacks, desserts, beef stew rice sets and even imported beer!

Relaxing atmosphere with great music with food and drinks at affordable prices. This is the place to go if you love to spend an afternoon or your evenings in a coffee shop.

I had the worst house special blend coffee ever at this cafe. It tasted exactly like cheap 3-in-1 coffee. I was so surprised so I asked the shop owner why the house special blend coffee was with milk and sugar and tasted like 3-in-1? She just replied it's how they make it and said it uses same coffee beans like the americano my friend ordered. Are you kidding me? I pay NTD120 for house special when the americano only costs NTD100 just because you "helped" to "blend" in the sugar and milk that I don't need? And come on, even Starbucks gives milk and sugar without extra charge. I tried my friend's americano and I can guarantee you it's not the same coffee beans used in the so called "house special blend". I can tolerate the rundown place, but zero tolerance to the poor quality 3-in-1 in a cafe that claims themselves offer boutique coffee beans.

Expensive cheap food and drinks. You come here for the stellar vibe which ranges from a dark and cozy to a loud and vibrant feel depending on the time of day. I love the atmosphere for studying or reading, but I can’t get over the prices and some parts of the floor seem like they are about to fail at any moment. Still a great place to bring a friend for a chat if you’ve got the money to throw around but not somewhere to go every single day.

The ambiance and vibes are nice, but the service is terrible. The staff are pretty unfriendly (dismissive towards questions about the menu) and told me off when I tried to charge my laptop. I rarely give negative reviews but don't recommend this place to anyone.

I've been a big fan of this place for years, and it's great to see that their move to a new location has put them back in the game. Despite a more comfortable and spacious premises, they still have the "friendly little jazz cafe vibe". Coffee is good as always, food menu is so-so as always, apparently run by the same (friendly) family as always. A great place to spend an evening with friends, but keep in mind the meal choices are pretty limited, so maybe best to stick with the beverage menu.

places.name: 2730café

plus_code.compound_code: 2HM4+CR 大安區 台灣台北市

places.formatted_address: No. 288號, Yanji St, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text:
Had a very relaxing evening during pouring rain last night. I’m visiting town for conference and just happened to run into this place not knowing what to expect and WOW, what a cute cafe full of surprises! Cozy environment, cute cats, friendly owners, everything in the store was very comforting.

The food was hearty (I ordered braised beef rice and pan-fried dumplings) and the milk tea tasted very fresh (I think it was meant to be sweet and I asked for little sweet assuming US standard, here I think that means more like 10% sweetness). Seemed like they also have a pretty unique craft beer selection as well, but they were out of the toasty lager so I didn’t get to try the beers…

If you want to get the vibe of how the locals really live, I’d take a visit once in a while!

You gotta love this place if you’re a cat lover. It’s not a cat cafe, but you can see a few cute cats playing around who don’t care about your existence 😂. Before entering or leaving, don't forget to inform the staff because they need to check on the cats first.

As for the vibe, it’s a nice place to work or study. You can stay here without a time limit, and there are sockets for charging everywhere. Their drinks and food are great.

They have strict rules for booking on weekends and weekdays, so please read the rules on their Line account or page first.

The fluffiest, cutest cheesecake I've ever had! It was great. The fruit tea was good too.
Very warm and cozy atmosphere. They have three cats, I saw the black cat mostly, the other two only came out for food 🤣
Very strict rules in the café, because of the limited seats and the cats. Somehow quite annoyed but had to follow anyway.

Overall is fine.
Yet, the white cat bit me all of a sudden.  I highly recommend the store owner to give a heads-up.
The milk tea is good but the chocolate cake is super thick. The cats don’t  look healthy. It’s too bad because otherwise the cafe has a nice mood

places.name: Block & Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 3G28+83 建明里 台灣台北市大同區

places.formatted_address: 103013, Taiwan, Taipei City, Datong District, Taiyuan Rd, 50號2樓

reviews.text: Just another cafe. Hard to find, hard to climb up to, drink was average, matcha latte full of ice, and I didn't even finish it in the end. Minimum one drink per person but we didn't even stay for long. Server didn't have initiative to make the eat-in cafe latte first, made the to-go matcha latte first instead. Even though we ordered the cafe latte first. If grabbing to go, not worth it.
Pretty good coffee served in a mug. Tasted pretty good but was a tad too frothy. Wife had an iced matcha latte which she thought was too sweet. Service was ok, and ambience was also nothing special.
Really enjoyed my coffee and the decor in the second room ^^ it was peaceful - on a second floor. Staff is attentive and so kind. Thank you 💜 Cat gave me company for a bit hehe

Upstairs cafe with a menu of espresso and tea. The cafe is more of a study spot with lots of people on laptops working quietly. The drinks are on the pricier side and OK at best in terms of flavor, but it’s a good place to unwind for a bit with wifi. No food available in case you want a snack with your drink.

Hidden gem of Taipei! Delicious coffee, teas, breakfast and cakes. The atmosphere is super relaxed with some chill jazz music. You can spend there easily the whole day just going through the menu (Chinese with some English titles and pictures). Highly recommendable!

places.name: Coffee sind

plus_code.compound_code: 2GRJ+CV 幸市里 台灣台北市中正區

places.formatted_address: No. 8號, Lane 56, Section 1, Xinsheng S Rd, Zhongzheng District, Taipei City, Taiwan 100

reviews.text: visited this awesome cafe during my stay in Taipei. Everything was perfect, the Barista is so friendly and offered me their special drip coffee to try. I ordered oats latte, it's a medium roast, so good!

I don’t come here often because I’m not living in Taipei much now. But it is always a must for me. I can’t recommend this spot to people enough. The vibe, energy, creativity and attention to details. Never fails.

The baristas there are always showing you the best of themselves, despite the rush of crowd or the unpredictable weather, they are always patient to explain the drink for you and giving out their lovely energy to everyone. I am always inspired coming here being a barista and hospitality  worker myself. Love how they work with local grown ingredients too. Thank you all for providing this beautiful place and vibe to us.

Oh my.. tiny tiny cafe.
Employees were nice and helpful but …
The wait was toooo long on the weekend :(
Lots of people were sitting and the ground waiting for their coffee. Even the takeaways take a long time.

We have returned here for the great Chikan Black Sugar Latte! It’s a tiny shop, but the environment is very chill! The guy who makes it was there again today! He did another fantastic job and he speaks English, too! ☺️ They have great customer service also! We will be back when we visit again!

This the best coffee place in Taipei😍
I had a cappuccino and cake
The cake was delicious too!!🍰

Leo and Mini were extraordinary kind and made me feel very welcome!

places.name: YABOO Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 2GJJ+56 福住里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: No. 26, Lane 41, Yongkang St, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text: This is one cafe that I always would prefer to go post-evening hours. They are kind and generous. They offer charging facilities around almost all the tables. Although the parking space next to the coffee shop might not be enough at all times but I mostly able to get one during late night (usually after 10 PM).

Tiramisu is tasty, and the atmosphere is pleasant. This location is ideal for catching up with friends. This cafe comes highly recommended. Everything is perfect! This location gets 5 stars.

Drinks and food are also great! Keep up the good work!

Awesome cafe, perfect atmosphere for work.The tiramisu and chocolate/banana cakes are just 😍. The A/C is quite strong, so it's a bit cold sometime, take something warm to wear, even during summer. They also have some tables and plugs outside.
There is now a 3 hours limit
Delicious coffee with options including oat milk and added alcohol (kahlua/frangelico/amaretto etc). Great spot to sit and relax. Highly recommend the iced alcoholic lattes.

Had a fantastic experience tonight.  I strolled in with no expectations and was blown away.  The staff was very welcoming and guided to a seat.  Despite my broken mandarin I was able to order a hand drip coffee. I watched as the barista carefully made the pour over and tasted it before approving the carafe to be sent over to me. The Ethiopia G1 was delicious and the notes were just as described fruity, vibrant, and juicy.  I wanted to try a cup of the house blend beans as well but apparently that is for espresso only.  Perhaps the barista took pity on me because gave me a cup of something on the house. Unfortunately I was too late to order an espresso because earlier I saw him methodically take off the hopper and store the beans and clean out the espresso grinder.  10/10 experience, even more so being at 11pm.  I'll be back tomorrow morning to grab an espresso!

places.name: Daychill Specialty Coffee Co.

plus_code.compound_code: 3H25+QJ 東光里 台灣台北市松山區

places.formatted_address: No. 55-1號, Section 5, Nanjing E Rd, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 105

reviews.text:
Strong flavor coffee, deserts were surprisingly tasty!
Super chill place for chitchatting and working. Clean & bright environment, great atmosphere, staffs are also very friendly.

Minus point is cash payment only.

Been wanted to check out this place, finally get a chance.

First of all, all beans are available for smell, so you can smell it first then decided which one you’d like to choose. Because it’s my first time there so define my wanna try one of their specialty. After smelling beans, I decided to go for- DayChill specialty chocolate girls, using siphon. ( Siphon and pour over same price)

Nice presentation with explanation of the beans. The chocolate girl really tastes like her name: nuts, butter, chocolate with hint of cocoa. Love it.

My friend ordered geisha one, great as well.
We also tasted the Tieguanyin Basque Cheesecake it was great! ( but I kept hearing customers asking about lemon tart and they sold out today lol)

I think I’ll definitely come check out here again to taste different beans.

The sweetness of Sicilian coffee(160) can be adjusted, the sweetness lowest level is quite fine.
The ”Financier“(120) is good, but the Earl Gray Tea flavor has strong aroma and sweet. The original one I felt more better.
I like French sash and every table has a socket, except for the multi-person round table beside the door.
Clean washroom.

Delicious latte and mocha! It seems taste thicker than usual latte.

Very chill vibes in the cafe with most people just doing some work on their laptops.

Came here during a weekday afternoon. The place was quite and perfect to get some work done. Hand drip coffee was very good - the flavour was delicate but balanced. I enjoyed it. Would come back to try their desserts too.

places.name: STARBUCKS Dingxi

plus_code.compound_code: 2G78+84 後溪里 台灣新北市永和區

places.formatted_address: No. 181號, Section 2, Yonghe Rd, Yonghe District, New Taipei City, Taiwan 234

reviews.text:
I dropped in this shop as my 2nd time!
Many peoples at there!
Now 20:03, young peoples are majority of them !
Friday night and after their dinner they are rushed to hear this shop!
I order regular hot coffee!
I spend time for my citizen sketches at 1st floor of this shop !
There 2nd floor also for over 100 peoples capacity they have!

Manager has alot of attention to detail.  I left my hotel room card there and he called to notify so i returned to pick up.  His staff drops my fork from the tray to the table and replaces with a clean one.   Many seating upstairs filled with many with their laptops but nice cafe vibe.  Loved the ice almond milk latte in the glass rather than a plastic cup which really made a enjoyment for me.  Unfortunately, my penne wasn’t completely warmed up so only 4 stars for the food.
The place is nice, clean. I usually come here quite often for meetings with friends or when I need to work a little bit. There are not a big choice of food, but can grab some drink and desserts.

Relaxing and calm place. The place was quite full while I was there and most people were studying or tutoring. Not bad but the toilet needs a lot of improvement. It was dirty when I were there. And what I have noticed is that Starbucks here does not separate the toilet for women and men. There is just one toilet.
Chill place for gathering. Friendly barista with good in speak english at 5 P.M today.

places.name: 珈琲 寶山

plus_code.compound_code: 2GXC+X6 中山區 台灣台北市

places.formatted_address: No. 36號, Chang'an W Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 104

reviews.text:
Nice place.

I tried their house blend, Geisha, and El Salvador. My favourite was El Salvador. Panama Geisha was tea-alike which is a trend nowadays and well prepared by the barista, however, El Salvador had more obvious notes.

I will totally recommend this place. It has a lot of character.

Quality coffee in a cosy cafe for people who like coffee and quality time to chill with some very nice stereo music in the backdrop. Not for those who are just looking for a place to chat in a group or have a lively conversation.

I have tried two hand-drip coffee: 鳶 (deep roast) 22g/70ml and Jamaica Blue Mountain single origin, which are both very nice.

Love those vintage speakers and very good vibe , great music taste. Not to mention coffee was top tier as well. Great shop. Love the kumquat ice coffee!  And royal hot coffee, both are highly Recommend!
Old Japanese style coffee shop in town offering nel drip coffee.  High quality hand drip coffee and quiet space.
It was a great experience! I stumbled upon this cafe while traveling. Very friendly, kind, and comfortable! Coffees are good as well.

places.name: 伴鹿咖啡Deerfriend Café

plus_code.compound_code: 2GGX+GP 全安里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Section 2, Dunhua S Rd, 203號4F

reviews.text:
Extraordinary coffee selection and skills. The staffs are very friendly and professional on what they serve. Even though the desert option is not much, but with all fine quality.

Strongly recommend!!

Under the radar due to its location on the 4th floor of a plain-looking walk-up, this cafe offers a selection of single-origin coffee at a mere NTD200 (roughly 4-5 cups). The coffee latte I tried was pretty smooth, even when it was left sitting out. If you fancy a view of the city, go for their window seats, which overlook the hustle and bustle of the Xinyi shopping district.

Stumbled upon this place randomly while walking around. It's definitely off the beaten path a bit as another reviewer said. After a short stair climb up, you'll be greeted by a small, hipster-esque cafe that takes a ton of pride in their craft.

The barista is indeed extremely knowledgeable and speaks English extremely proficiently. Shoot for a window seat to enjoy the views and people watch while sipping on some truly memorable coffee.

The cakes are must try! Especially the brownie which comes randomly from the afternoon tea set(300 NTD).
They serve really good cold dripped coffee too!
beautiful view, nice staff, pleasant environment.

places.name: McCafé 咖啡-台北莊敬店

plus_code.compound_code: 2HG9+Q6 三張里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: No. 475號, Zhuangjing Rd, Xinyi District, Taipei City, Taiwan 110

reviews.text: Nmjmmr mea3nxxxñnxe333xxxxx33x. Eezz

McDonald's breakfast has a high CP value and a variety of choices (but I mostly choose Manfu Burger). The buns at Manfu Burger may not be as soft as hamburger buns (hamburger buns are more suitable for children), but they are full of bite and worth savoring!
However, I also think that McDonald's has learned a bad lesson. In order to support McCafe, it often tries to upgrade the coffee or adjust the price. Because there is a 7-11 across the road, and what's even more lamentable is that there is a Cama Coffee next to it.
Therefore, I have been ordering a Full Burger at McDonald's recently, walking to Cana across the street to buy an American or vanilla latte, and then returning to McDonald's to get a Full Burger. I feel full of happiness and have a huge CP value!
You...you can try it too!

You can also order directly at the open coffee bar
This time I ordered hot chocolate, Assam milk tea and cinnamon rolls, and got a 10 yuan discount on bread and drinks👍
The friendly barista sprinkles favorite chocolate powder
The whole cup of hot chocolate is so delicious
The full range of coffee drinks are freshly ground to order. It takes a little waiting time, but the delicious coffee is worth the wait♥
Cinnamon rolls are baked every morning around 7 to 8 o'clock. They are soft on the outside and fragrant with cinnamon on the inside. The chocolate croissant tastes bitter-sweet and soft on the outside. People who don't like too sweet can give it a try.
Assam and matcha milk tea are also great
Each one is rich and fragrant
The price is cheap, and there are discounts for packages.
I tried cinnamon rolls for the first time. They felt like they were freshly baked. They were so delicious. Then the fresh milk tea had latte art on top. It was so amazing😱
The aroma of coffee is pure and mellow~the handmade milk foam is dense and delicious ❤❤❤~the cinnamon roll croissant is delicious🤤🤤🤤 Come and have a cup of afternoon tea to be happy and content😘😘😘

places.name: nido

plus_code.compound_code: 2HR9+FM 興雅里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: 110, Taiwan, Taipei City, Xinyi District, Section 5 of Zhongxiao East RoadSection 5 of Zhongxiao E Rd, 183號2樓

reviews.text: If you’re looking for a quiet place for reading, working, and spending time alone, this cafe is made for you. It’s not for chitchatting, or friends gathering. I’m ok with the quiet rules but the owner or staff’s attitude should be improved. Plus, the menu price is quite high for just a ☕️ (The taste was average)

Offering a silent, almost meditative oasis away from the bustle of busy Taipei I am pleasantly surprised to enjoy the low volume suggestion here because there is space and time to drink in the chill vibe that Nido has.

Coffee is decent and the cheesecake is a winner for sure! Will definitely be back when I can but in the meantime, I’ll just sink into the quiet ambience that has been so intentionally curated here!

For anyone else who can't find this, see the photos for the outside view, and which button to press. Inside is very calm and quiet, gentle soothing music. Prices are interesting: 300 for first item, 100 for each subsequent item. It was too quiet for me, I didn't stay, but rated it 5*, because if you are looking for a peaceful quiet clean calm place, this seems like a reasonable place to be :)

A great place to study or work on stuffs with how chill and peaceful the ambience is!! Only light whispering is allowed and it honestly helps with productivity A LOT. There’s still chill music played in the back so it’s not awkwardly silent. The owner is super cool and definitely puts a lot of effort into running this cafe, and the service and food is amazing. The blueberry cheesecake was so good that I know if I return I’d get it again and again.

I LOVE this place. It’s VERY quiet, cake (peanut butter cheesecake) and coffee are great. Very suitable for people who prefer some alone-time and quiet time. Not a big place so they can’t fit in big group size - which is good so the loudness can be controlled.

places.name: Café Costumice

plus_code.compound_code: 2HV3+G2 建安里 台灣台北市大安區

places.vicinity: 忠孝東路四段223巷71弄6號1樓
places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Alley 71, Lane 223, Section 4, Zhongxiao E Rd, 6號1樓

reviews.text:
UPDATED (5->3 stars⭐)
Went back two more times and started to see the inconsistency in both service quality and coffee making skills... In the most recent visit, it seems like the barista is less experienced and the milk didn't froth well... I pointed it out to the server and a more experienced barista made us a new one.

Regarding service, the male servers are usually fine but there's this female server who seems like she doesn't care at all...

FIRST VISIT (5 stars⭐)
Flat white with Ethiopia beans is so good! It's a medium light roast with very floral notes but without the acidity. Highly recommend!

There were many seats inside and plenty of charging outlets available. WiFi is free and reliable. Great for working (if you don't need to be in meetings).
Dark moody vibes. One of the vibiest cafes in the dongqu area. They have indoor and outdoor seating with a couple large long tables. Came for coffee but definitely want to come back for drinks too.

Taiwan has an awesome coffee scene and this place doesn’t disappoint. With indoors and outdoors space (try the small chairs outside), the coffee is amazing. The have “regular coffee” and “serious coffee”

I tried the Guatemala pour over (serious type) and while I am an espresso type of person, this taste made me want to try pour overs again.

Price wise is on the high end of the spectrum but you pay for ultra quality.

I also saw the have a big variety of wines and craft beers. Didn’t try the food or cakes.

This is a nice cafe if you’re looking for a cool working space, as they have charging sockets indoor and outdoor. The coffee and food were okay (average), but a bit expensive with service charges. I think I pay for a nice atmosphere and their service cuz they don’t have limited time for sitting there and also the staff were nice and kept refilling water for customers. Apart from the coffee, they have craft beers tap as well.
Great coffee and atmosphere.  Very chill and doesn’t get loud.  Outdoor seating is my favorite.

places.name: 六丁目

plus_code.compound_code: 3H56+99 介壽里 台灣台北市松山區

places.formatted_address: No. 7號, Lane 6, Xinzhong St, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 105

reviews.text: Had an amazing cold matcha latte and banana chocolate cake, the atmosphere is serene and relaxing, small place, quiet, not for large groups though

One of the best cafes with excellent matcha dessert in town, if you’re a matcha lover, you can’t miss this one. Their dessert will not disappoint you, literally.
The other dessert we had was yogurt cheese cake with a slice of peach which was also delicious.
And it feels good to be dining in door after the lockdown, although we can’t see each other’s face with the board between us, but at least we got back to civilization !

Cute casual coffee shop serving perfectly made oat milk cappuccino, matcha lattes and my personal favorite candied lemon iced coffee. We also ordered banoffie pie, yogurt cheesecake and chocolate tea tart, all of which we throughly enjoyed. Cute cafe to chill for a chat over great coffee and cakes.

By far one of my new favorite places to get matcha cake in all of Taipei. The decor is very cozy and homey with small works of ceramics laid out near the window. All the drinks I've tried have also been very unique and delicious (black sesame latte and black sugar latte with crean foam). You can even order 8" birthday cakes on three days notice for special occasions!

Love the music and vibe here.
Service super nice staffs are super friendly.
Definitely a place for working or just spend some time alone or with a friend.
Prices so not expensive and they open until 22:00pm. I will come back for sure! Oh forget to mention, tasty food and drinks!

places.name: Kaldi coffee

plus_code.compound_code: 2HH4+42 臨江里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: No. 10號, Alley 24, Lane 165, Tonghua St, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text: Lot of different coffee to choose from. And quite spacious with electrical outlets for your laptop. Good place to hang.
Like the window seats that gives you the view of the passers-by in an air-conditioned room.
A lovely unassuming coffee shop with snacks and entrees. Great to check out if you’ve time to sit and enjoy.  Tons of beans and varieties.
Old fashion but pretty good place to relax
Good strong coffee. Decent WiFi, bookshelf after bookshelf of manga, with soft background music. They also have a decent lasagna for Taiwan.

places.name: 85°C Bakery Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 2G67+QX 信義里 台灣新北市永和區

places.formatted_address: No. 105號, Section 2, Yonghe Rd, Yonghe District, New Taipei City, Taiwan 234

reviews.text: Cake is okay. I supposed to get a hot, melty and creamy egg tart, however it was cold instead. One star plus is for the cashier who is very supportive and friendly although he can't speak English. Maybe I will not come back as I am in the hunt of best egg tarts in Taipei.

I can understand the evening time can get quite busy but that is no reason to be absolutely rude to customers. The person at the counter literally shouted and was not even ready to listen. Living in Taipei for 2 years now never have I ever had such horrible experience. Not going to visit again.

I'm a regular here when I visit, and this place was the first 85°C bakery. It's the original, and the food is good. There is also one in Sacramento, and the vanilla latte is great. Service is good, and the atmosphere was very lively.

The cakes and breads are OK, but the cashiers are not friendly and often times they are hostile!

Food - 3
Service - 1
Come here for breads regularly. Good variety.  We get cakes here for birthdays and other occasions too.

places.name: 兜麥咖啡大安店

plus_code.compound_code: 2GFV+9F 臥龍里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Section 2, Fuxing S Rd, 341號一樓

reviews.text:
Amazing, cozy atmosphere, you can have great espresso, drip coffee, latte or I would suggest the awesome brown sugar latte! (See picture)
The owner is very nice and friendly, a must go for coffee in the area!

Definitely a coffee-person’s spot — there’s a list of different blends + bean origins on the expanded menu. The staff seem to be constantly making 手沖 pour-overs to sample + taste, and are happy to respond to any questions or curiosity. For NT $500 you can buy membership, though I didn’t ask about the details. There is some English on signs + the menu, but a lot of the info I saw was in Chinese. Ask to see what the daily toasts and desserts are as there’s no display. Overall, a pleasant cafe w a 2nd level (low ceiling) + friendly vibe; expect to spend ~ NT 200+ for just coffee. The tiramisu I had was a bit over-soaked + bitter.
My favorite neighborhood café. Ambiance is chill and the owner is just lovely. Thier brown sugar latte is to die for ❤️
good coffee, comfortable chair, nice staff
The coffee is delicious and the hostess explains it kindly. There are seats on the second floor but the height is low.

First,  its the best Starbucks with amazing view in Taipei

Staff are very helpful and welcoming 🙏

Speak English very well and help me to choose healthy breakfast and delicious of course by Starbucks

The shop located infront linsen park with magical view you can enjoy specially at morning

Highly recommended
Highly appreciated

Top notch service! Crew were very friendly and spoke some English which made our stay a lot more comfortable. My partner bought a cute cup and he received tons of gifts! We were also able to get our bottles refilled before we left.

Wifi was also decent. We were able to send mails and post on social media without problems.

Small Starbucks, pretty empty on a weekday early morning. I just that may explain the low energy level of the counter staff.

The big attraction and drawback about this shop that it is opposite the park. There’s a lovely green vista through the window which is special in the city but every mosquito and his friend are trying to get through the cracks in the door and have their breakfast too.

Unfortunately served by an impolite staff, who did not seem to like children, frowning and making faces, annoyingly telling me to stop my son when he played with the "caution wet floor" stand that was placed in the waiting line. I asked for coffee to drink here, so please give me in a mug cup. She answers, sounding upset a bit: i know 😮‍💨
Unpleasant morning coffee for me🙃
Soooooo slow herelp

places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, Lane 143, Section 3, Ren'ai Rd, 38號1F

reviews.text:
📍 Awake til sleep, Taipei 🇹🇼

🥖 肉丸三明治加蛋 Meatball Bahn Mi （$110）
Beef Bahn Mi was unavailable, so this was recommended by the owner. I personally found it just average. The vegetables were fresh and the sauce was also good! However, the meatballs had some little chunks of fat and meat that were hard to chew. I also wished there were more vegetables.

Environment: Although the cafe was just small, the atmosphere was really pleasant and warm. The owner welcomed customers with a bright smile and was very efficient in her service 👌 also loved their music!

Overall: The flavor of the sandwich was acceptable but a bit underwhelming. Not a fan of their meatballs, but I’d go back to try out the other flavors and their coffee! The lady owner was very accommodating and welcoming.

Good latte and egg sandwich for a quick lunch.
Cosy and not as large inside as photos suggest.
Cash only.
Nice friendly service.
Came in Friday late noon, and they only offered three selection of Vietnamese sandwiches.  Sandwich is not really Vietnamese taste. Iced Vietnamese coffee is good.

A very beautiful cafe. The owners are really nice and friendly. The space is small but the coffee is great. Tiramisu Latte is must try. The taste was amazing and refreshing. Espresso and citrus tea were also great.
Good banh mi and nice to have some Vietnamese coffee.

places.name: Weiyang Coffee

plus_code.compound_code: 2GGW+FX 群賢里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: No. 10, Lane 208, Siwei Rd, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text: Lucky us to have the seats without reservation in weekend. Love the whole vibe of this cafe, a bit vintage decoration, chill music and comfort environment. Great place to relax, casual work or chit chatting. They offer a lot of mangas. Bailey’s latte coffee was tasty, iced black coffee has quite strong flavor. Wanna taste the sweets next time. Minus point is cash payment only, hope they have linepay soon.

This midnight cafe is exactly what it meant!!! It is quiet and unique! Every single customer is with their laptop, or iPad, or iPhone, or Samsung Galaxy! Unfortunately for us, this place wasn't meant for four of us who just needed the second place to chat after our ”second partyplace ”! The latte ad matcha cheesecakes were immensely delicious!!! We ended up sitting outside since it doesn't fit the atmosphere to sit inside! The bench outside was perfect for us! We had food time until the time to leave for us at 12:30 am!

Beautiful vintage coffee shop with a good selection of drinks, desserts, and mangas! It's pet friendly and has a more relaxed atmosphere compared to some of the more work-oriented cafes I usually go to.

I'd recommend this coffee shop if you want a more laid back atmosphere to hang out with your friends!
Very chill place for late night coffees. Pretty quiet inside but good enough to have a pleasant chat. Parking is horrible if you drive just FYI.

The whole vibe was chill, and the music was easy to listen to💙
I tried its “Cat Rice,” taste special! And its brown sugar milk (I ordered hot one) was excellent!!!
Good place to chat with your friend ( in a lower voice would be better), read, or enjoy your time. However, the lighting was a bit weak, so if you’re gonna look at the screen for a long time, I wouldn’t suggest you to be here, or else it might harm your eyes!

places.name: Louisa Coffee

plus_code.compound_code: 3G7C+6R 集英里 台灣台北市中山區

places.formatted_address: No. 3號, Minquan W Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491

reviews.text: Honestly, it's my first time visiting this store, and I was really disappointing. This place was incredibly messy and dirty. I’m definitely not planning on coming back. You seriously need more staff to clean the restrooms, tidy up the counters, and restock the paper towels. Absolutely not recommended.

Relaxing and amazing staff. Thanks to the guy staff who fluently speak English so can take my order perfectly. Thanks to you man. You have an excellent English speaking accent.finally found a coffee shop I am comfortable ✋👍

Nice spacious space with 3 floors. But too many people and too dirty. Floor is sticking to my shoes, bathroom toilet is really dirty.  The staffs are too busy and it takes 15 mins for a coffee even when I’m here at noon on a weekday.
The owner definitely can do better in renovating the space, everything is dated and tearing up. Such a shame

I had a very pleasant experience at this Louisa Coffee. Clean environment and very comfortable interior design. The items sold at this store were like usually at a Louisa Coffee of good reliable good quality.

I would like to especially emphasise the friendly service of the service personal, the cashier was very friendly and patient eventhough my Chinese is not perfect, she also reminded me to be careful since the drink was hot, excellent friendly service!

Perfect place to sit back and enjoy a cup of coffee.
It’s clean, fast service and very conveniently located.
We sat at the coffee shop after our hike at Elephant Mountain, before heading back to hotel.

places.name: Fika Fika Cafe A13

plus_code.compound_code: 2HP9+P4 西村里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: 110, Taiwan, Taipei City, Xinyi District, Songren Rd, 58號 號B3

reviews.text: Fika offers high-quality coffee with a minimalist, Nordic-inspired interior. Prices are on the higher end, but the coffee and ambiance make it worth it. It’s a good place to take a break. They also sell beans that make for nice gifts

Overall great coffee! But if you're buying speciality coffee bean boxes be wary of empty satchels (these are sample boxes that are identical to the product).

Attended Fika Fika on a lazy Sunday early afternoon. It was very busy although that might be attributable to the holiday period.

The ambience was good. Decor was reminiscent of a certain Scandinavian brand. Minimalistic and pleasant. Service was great, we were asked if we were enjoying our coffee on three separate occasions (perhaps because of our intense gazes). But I will just give bonus points for engaged service. I am big fan of their prominently featured nonconventional styled espresso machine.

We had two filter coffees and the coffee soft serve.

The coffee soft serve was great. It was a very light coffee taste with a sprinkling of ganache. The combination of crunch and soft serve was great and the mild coffee flavour definitely gave it a more dessert(y) feel.

For the coffee we had the Colombian Villa Clara Estate Washed. It is labelled a caramel and nut flavour profile (and you certainly get that aroma if you let it sit) but I found more often the flavour profile was a wild floral.

We also ordered the Taiwan Nanshou Baisheng Village 68 Hours Anoerobic Fermentation. That was a very interesting experience. There is a fermented bean element there, it was a coffee that certainly seemed to be reminiscent of Taiwanese food. I also got a slight mantou bun flavour on the back of the tongue. It tasted like a medium/dark roast. If you go in with the expectation of something a little unusual that tastes more like an accompaniment to a meal than an afternoon coffee it should go well.

Great! They have tons of options for everyone and it’s always a nice calming environment.
My gym teacher always stops in every morning to get a juice and swears on his life that it’s the reason he stays so healthy!
The breakfast sandwiches are always perfect! A great pick me up when you come in.
Definitely come here is you’re looking for a good neighborhood spot before you start your day.

Superb!
This place has not disappointed.  They have a more homemade taste compared to your chain coffee locations.  To my surprise and delight they were able to make a Late with Oat Milk.  So so good!

Coffee would be without saying one of the best in town! We’ve got some dessert this visit. The cheesecake and pudding are both tasty. Waffle is not quiet unique and would not personally reorder for future visit.

We were there on a busy Sunday afternoon. Staffs were still friendly to arrange seats for 5 of us. Waffle was soso, earl grey pound cake and cinnamon apple pie as well as caramel pudding were great. We ordered an ice coffee, sea salt caramel latte, a Mocha , a Columbia and an Ethiopian got coffee, everyone was happy with her order. If anything to complain is that the seats were not so comfortable.

places.name: Louisa Coffee 路易莎咖啡(合江門市)

plus_code.compound_code: 3G4Q+5M 朱馥里 台灣台北市中山區

places.formatted_address: 104, Taiwan, Taipei City, Zhongshan District, Hejiang St, 27號29號1樓

reviews.text:
I came here in the rain after an afternoon meeting. It's located right across from the park in front of me, and looks like it's been renovated recently with a new look! It's a self-ordering system using a QR cord. As a member, I can prepare and pay! I ordered my usual chicken sandwich and fruit tea. Urban citizen sketches !
It’s new place and good atmosphere they have ! Service was good and nice shop !

Facing the park atmosphere, good food and delicious food, everyone can enjoy a wonderful afternoon tea here, so that everyone can enjoy a good time here. It is such a meeting and drinking coffee for office workers.

I live nearby, and because the store next door doesn’t sell specialty coffee, I have to buy this one occasionally. I’ve given it many chances, but it’s never been good! Must comment today. First of all, the basic egg burgers, ham and egg burgers, etc... taste very dry and must be said to be unpalatable. No peanut butter at all. Every one of the Neihu and Nangang restaurants I have eaten at is better than this one. Today I added an extra $15 to add sauce. But it’s still this kind of virtue.
I came to take out two cups of coffee and this egg burger. I wanted to be environmentally friendly, so I hoped for a cup holder. Xiao Qi would also take the initiative to ask. It is convenient for customers to take, and it is insulated so that it will not burn your hands. I asked her, but they gave it It was like this. My hands were really burned to death when I took it back. Moreover, the material was so soft that it couldn’t support the weight of the coffee. I was so afraid that he would pour it. It sucks! So it's only a few steps away and I don't want to buy a bag. But it’s too bad that you offer this! There is no sense of any enthusiasm for customer service in this store! and value. Don't push

Other Louisa Coffee branches do not require customers to scan the QR code to order food. I guess it is because this store is special. Because I was not used to scanning the QR code to order food, I missed the opportunity to collect points with my black card, so I had to give the service 2 stars because the service of the clerk was limited to assisting the guests to scan the QR code. And if you go to the restroom after finishing your drinks, they will be taken away. If you still want to keep your seat, please throw away more debris.

Dining environment: 80 points
Service attitude: 85 points
Delicious meal: 90 points

Thoughts: I personally think that the dining environment in this restaurant is relatively crowded in Louisa. Each seat is actually very crowded, so I personally don’t feel very comfortable when doing it, especially if I say something, I will almost always be ignored. I heard that there was only one counter service person in the whole store. I stayed there for two hours and there was only one person, so it was basically too busy. I ordered a cup of fruit tea and just waited for the fruit tea to be ready. , so it takes almost 15 minutes. I personally think it is a bit long, but the service attitude of the counter staff is good and they are smiling. The clean environment on site is clean. As for the price, I think the price is really good. A pretty cheap fruit tea, if I remember correctly it was $60. I drank it hot and it tasted really good. You can also adjust the sweetness. Overall, Louisa’s products are high quality and affordable, regardless of the method or mobile payment method. Option, it’s okay to come over with friends to chat occasionally, but if you want to tell secrets, it may not be really suitable.

places.name: BorgesPlace

plus_code.compound_code: 3G88+7W 蓬萊里 台灣台北市大同區

places.formatted_address: No. 22號, Changji St, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 103

reviews.text: I've walked by a few times and found it beautiful. Finally I had the chance to come in for breakfast and coffee. The interior is nicely designed and the service is friendly. I don't mind the two hour time restrictions on busy days. Next time gotta try the desserts instead

Bribes guests for a 5-star review. Overpriced. The only place I’ve paid $8 USD for an Iced Latte was Beverly Hills. It hurt, but at least it was 90210.

Despite the bad, the service was pleasant. The bagel sandwich was edible. I refused to pay $240NT for an Iced Latte so I walked down the street to a much more reasonable coffee shop.
It’s a good place to have afternoon tea and brunch. Tiramisu is the best dessert in this area. It’s also impressed of chips, it’s crispy. Recommend people stay in Taipei could come and give a try.
Great food and service, best cakes ! Good location near MRT station !
Place is very cosy & relaxing. Service staff are very po& helpful. Loved the vibes & food here. Recommended to visit this place

places.name: 2J CAFE

plus_code.compound_code: 2GJQ+98 龍圖里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: No. 9, Lane 79, Section 2, Jianguo S Rd, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text: Very atmospheric brasserie with friendly service and nice food. This is a relatively quiet place, and it can get busy on holidays. Not the cheapest, but very nice food and a pleasant place to relax or work a bit on your laptop.

I absolutely love 2J Cafe. It's such a cute spot with a wide variety of things to order—coffee, food, beer, and cakes.

They have both outdoor seating with a cute garden and a nicely decorated indoor area.

The staff is incredibly nice; when it started raining, they helped us move our table and even offered free cake because we had to move a few times!

It's a chill and adorable place, perfect for meeting up with friends, working, or studying. Highly recommend!

Sweet little cafe to spend an idle afternoon. Only had drinks there, didn’t try the food. Coffee’s good. Great place to take photos. We walked there, got the opportunity to walk through Taipei’s residential area. Which is a nice experience too.

An wonderful cafe located near the biggest park in the capital, with its old structure hidden between towering condos, covered by its own garden greenery. It has quite a few pleasant outdoor seats, and abundant of indoor seats. It offers a variety of desserts as well as savory delicacies. The kimchi fusion tortillas were amazingly tasty, the scones set and honey French toast were brilliant. Even though I prefer heavy cream to whipped cream on my scones, they still brought me satisfaction. The staff was nice and accommodating, the ambiance was chill, and the price was not bad.

Little chill cafe that has really great meals. The cafe is located in a really old house having 1st/2nd floor and a little small garden. It’s pretty comfortable sitting outside to enjoy the wind breeze. I recommend ordering the double cheese 🧀 🍕 and the fried chicken. The tteok bokki is too spicy 🌶, I don’t really suggest.

places.name: Wood x White Café

plus_code.compound_code: 2GWG+62 梅花里 台灣台北市中正區

places.formatted_address: No. 23-2號, Lane 9, Linsen N Rd, Zhongzheng District, Taipei City, Taiwan 100

reviews.text:
Love the vibe and atmosphere at this compact cafe, hidden inside an alleyway the wooden Reno  simply just works.

Unfortunately did not have a place to dine inside, managed to buy a cake for dessert - takeaway, the cake was well made and decadent, milky cream and high quality green seedless grapes filled inside 2 pieces of crispy biscuit like buns with mellow sweetness.

Well balanced dessert without too much sugar intake, loved it.
Desserts and drinks are just fine. The space will be better if some customers can lower their voice.
A cute little cafe! Their matcha latte is really good. Their tarts and cakes are also recommended! I hope they start accepting card payment soon; they only accept cash or 街口 right now.

Great place to have some exquisite and delicate looking pastries. There isn't much options for salty dishes, and may not fill you, but their quiches are pretty tasty. Would recommend coming for afternoon tea and not empty stomached.
Their milk teas are really good too, quite a variety to choose from.
Enjoyed very much!
Very delicious tart! Lemon went well with matcha! And the matcha is so nice, was very smooth. The strawberry tea is surprisingly nice and flavourful!

places.name: HOHO DRINKS 台北信義

plus_code.compound_code: 2HR7+WM 新仁里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: No. 8號, Alley 16, Lane 559, Section 4, Zhongxiao E Rd, Xinyi District, Taipei City, Taiwan 110

reviews.text: Awesome coffee spot, ordered a 'Special Americano', its Americano but it tastes like latte, really unique coffee. The barista would charge gas into the caffe crema, making it a whole new tasting experience. Love the ambience, service was great, no complains!

Nice and friendly staff. Great atmosphere and great tea. (Didn’t have coffee that day but would love to pay another visit to try some)

Cozy, but not many seats. Would recommend to come for a small chat or takeaway.

I love this cafe! The employees are super friendly and lovely. They have quality tea, quality coffee, and the best damn toasted bread I've ever had. I don't wanna get your expectations of the toasted bread TOO high, but really, it's perfectly golden & crispy on the outside but softy & warm on the inside. Mmmm... Wonderful place.

Great coffee and toast. However, the opening time is not reliable at all. They say they open at 8am but half the time it's much later. For people heading in to work, getting coffee in the morning from HoHo is unreliable....

Staffs are really friendly and love to chat with you which makes me home.
The drink and toast are definitely worth to visit again again and again.

places.name: 85°C Bakery Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 2HG8+VF 三張里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: No. 416號, Zhuangjing Rd, Xinyi District, Taipei City, Taiwan 110

reviews.text: Service is good. Breads are always delicious as well as in Irvine, CA. Lots of specialized cakes. Must try coffee. The only thing that is different than in Irvine is that there are hamburgers on the menu. Very interesting.
Staff are amazing. One lady that works there. She works seemingly all day. But is always happy. Always smiles and me and my kid. Similarly the guy that works. There is friendly too.
Love the sea salt roasted oolong!
Not bad.
GOOD TASTE

places.name: The Singularity Co Working Space

html_attributions: 齊文藝室共享空間咖啡廳-The Singularity Co-Working Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 2GV8+PC 黎明里 台灣台北市中正區

places.formatted_address: No. 32號, Nanyang St, Zhongzheng District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10047

reviews.text:
I came here every week with the day pass! Nice place to do some work!

For the music, I would change time to time, I noticed that it is kind of the same most of the time.
However, it still deserves my 5 stars! 🤣

Cozy and great ambience! Very enjoy sitting as workshop.

Picked one of favourite drink and dessert. Orange americano was perfecto! Lava cake was just decent.

A great place near the Taipei Main Station for concentrated and quiet work. They have telephone booths available for rent where you can have online meetings or 2-people meetings for a little bit of privacy.

Drinks and snacks are available with no limit. And cakes are available for purchase.

Service is incredible. And the atmosphere is perfect for digital nomads. Tho it can get a little crowded for those who want a bit more personal space.

10/10 would recommend if you have the budget for it!

Nice workspace cafe on plan basis. Larger than expected with 3 levels and nicely decorated. Large choice of tea and free snacks included. Desserts as option. But Wifi a bit slow when crowded if you have large files.

I spent my whole day working here, and it was overall a great experience! The price includes snacks and drinks: personally, I particularly liked the selection of teas on offer, so I tried out a couple of different ones while I was there. It's also very convenient that you get to bring in food from outside. Very comfortable working space that I'd recommend to anyone looking for a spot where they can focus without having to worry about running out to get coffee or snacks whenever their energy dips (an issue Ive been having when working in the library). I'll definitely be returning!

places.name: Street churros taipei

plus_code.compound_code: 2HR4+5H 正聲里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: No. 24號, Lane 260, Guangfu S Rd, Da’an District, Taipei City, Taiwan 106

reviews.text:
A churro place that knows what they’re doing! They offer plenty of flavors and dipping options, which is always a plus. I love that they give you the choice between plain sugar or cinnamon sugar—since I’m not a huge fan of cinnamon but still love churros.

Their seasonal local flavors are also fun and delicious. And I have to say, the cream cheese dipping sauce is my guilty pleasure—I enjoyed every bite of it with this heavenly combination.

One thing I don’t get, though, is why so many drinks are always sold out, even when I go early…

The shop layout is a bit awkward, making it not the most comfortable place to dine in.

Nice cafe situated very near to Sun Yat Sen memorial hall. Staff were friendly and the place is big and comfortable. We ordered two types of churrus. Still piping hot. Sweetness level is acceptable. Tasty and goes very well with chocolate. Thumbs up for this place.
It is a little bit expensive, but it's delicious. Some drink taste sweet. And the dining environment is good。

Walked by in the evening and it was very busy. Looked very popular with queue outside waiting for takeout. So I came back the next morning at 10am to try. Got a seat immediately as quite empty in morning. Ordered black coffee and a cinnamon churros. Not bad. Similar to deep fried donut. Coffee was TWD105. No rush. Just sat for about an hour. They have free WiFi

The food is really good, but very pricey. The churros are definitely something you should get if you are going to the store. They also have fries which I personally think the flavor is a bit too strong, but many other people seem to like it. They have indoor and outdoor seating as well as free WiFi. The staff is friendly and patient. They make the churros fresh. They also have ice-cream scoops, but they are extremely expensive. They have a few other mealworthy dishes such as hamburgers and hot soup, but I have not tried them myself.

places.name: 85°C Daily Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 3G8R+C8 行仁里 台灣台北市中山區

places.formatted_address: No. 358號, Long Jiang Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491

reviews.text: I always love the coffe and their pieces of cake.
The cakes here are amazing and since they have cakes on demand it makes event planning much easier.
So much better than $tarbuck$!
Good of cake

It was so unpleasant. It was a popular sign for delivery. It was so hot that the bottom of the cup exploded. Even the delivery box was covered with it. The whole cup kept flowing until half the cup was left. I had to dispose of the whole cup and it burned my hands in the process. It was painful.

places.name: Simple Kaffa

plus_code.compound_code: 2HM7+GW 西村里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: No. 7號, Section 5, Xinyi Rd, Xinyi District, Taipei City, Taiwan 110

reviews.text:
Came for the view, stayed for the toast.
Visited Simple Kaffa Sola on Level 88 of Taipei 101, expecting just a stunning view—but ended up absolutely blown away by the food.

The whisky butter toast, cream cheese toast, sweet potato toast, and blue cheese cheesecake were all 5/5. Toast shouldn’t taste this good?! And the brown sugar latte? Out. Of. This. World.

We opted for a window seat (minimum spend NT$2,000 for 4 pax)—100% worth it. That view paired with incredible food? Unreal.

As soon as I stepped outside, I felt the FOMO hit.

I don’t even live here… when am I ever coming back?! Seriously unforgettable experience—come for the view, stay for everything else.

We seated by the window with great views of northern Taipei. We were greeted with friendly staff and easy atmosphere to enjoy our 90mins stay. The coffee was great; however, the food selection was very limited. The mocha cake was excellent! The other dishes were good but not outstanding. Consider this prime location, NT$500 per person was a great deal.

My friend and I really wanted to visit the observatory at 101 so we did some research and found this cafe! If you spend a certain amount of money you can sit closer to the window... What a deal! Great views with a nice little coffee and snack break. Couldn't ask for more! The coffee was really good and the desserts were delicious. Would highly recommend to check this place out!

I just want to say that the toast with whisky infused butter was mind blowing. It was a life changing experience for me.

Had a double shot of espresso (really on point!) and an alcoholic coffee option which was just magical!

Service was good either way the staff being very attentive.

No regrets. Love the ambiance and the coffee here. Will return!

The 88th storey from Taipei 101 isn’t the most beautiful city view to be frank. Spending in the place to gain access for photo is priced ok, for those who didn’t go before, this cafe price is considered affordable for the access. However the drink and bread is just normal. The almost two hours q is also something that you may need to make plans for especially if you have kids. Watch out for the weather too, you don’t want to pay 2000NTD on a bad weather and don’t get any views

The attitude of the clerk is very bad, the face is very stinky, like eating stool
Chair is slightly degraded
Cozy place for a chitchat
Cheap.

places.formatted_address: No. 23號, Lane 20, Section 2, Zhongshan N Rd, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491

reviews.text: Highly recommend the white almond milk tea - fragrant and quite unique. Nespresso milk tea was also good. Overall taste of drinks were great, though a bit pricier than usual

Ordered Best-seller milk tea, but it tastes so bad 😵‍💫😵‍💫
Sugar level is fixed
No bubble, no topping is sold

Came here recommendations from locals to try, and there was a line forming at the store already.

Thankfully, we were 4th in line, and the queue moved pretty fast. Ordered a typical milk tea 20% sugar, which is slightly pricier than average. Milk Tea wise leans towards the light and mild sweetness. Tea aroma is rather fragrant too. It's pretty good milk tea, but it's not worth the hype for a queue longer than 20 mins.
I ordered an original milk tea for today, It’s about $60. Nice milk tea with giant ice cube!
New style bubble tea experienced. A bit pricey but ok for their invention. But don't think worth the queue if there is more than 5 r queueing

places.name: Nearby Cafe 2

plus_code.compound_code: 2GW6+57 光復里 台灣台北市中正區

places.formatted_address: No. 37號, Yanping S Rd, Zhongzheng District, Taipei City, Taiwan 100

reviews.text:
An unsolicited very personal opinion of a non-expert average being in the search for the greatest 檸檬-西西里咖啡 in Taiwan.

Overall 西西里咖啡 rate - 4/5. Good, refreshing, and well-balanced.

Coffee: ✅ - on the soft side. Yet, it shows right when sipping and leaves a lasting fruity aftertaste that pairs up with the citrus of the lime.
Sweetness: ✅ - just about right. Lets the natural flavors of other ingredients show, specially the "natural" lemon sweetness.
Sourness: ✅ - soft acidity, natural lime taste, quite refreshing and zetsy.
Ice: 🆗 - about 1/2 of the glass. Which made the drink somewhat watery by the end.
Visuals: ✅ - esthetically pleasant and appealing. Fresh lime zest and slice, plus thyme leafs on top.
*The thyme pairs up nicely with both the citrus and coffee taste, specially as an aromatic aftertaste.

The place has a quite nice "fancy" and cozy atmosphere, perfect for chatting, hanging out, or working/studying. There's some background music. Lighting is a bit too bright. Staff is kind.

The chili noodles are delightful! I was warned that they were a little spicy, but it was truly just a little and didn't hurt my mouth or tongue at all. They paired excellently with the iced latte which had a rich deep flavor. The staff is very polite and communicated in English. I was very grateful for such wonderful food and service!

The atmosphere is comfortable. The most amazing thing is that the lady (who is really stylish btw) made all the food and drinks from just behind the cafe counter. I’m talking noodles, frittata and all. The chilli noodles was really yummy! Casual cafe food with a local twist 🫶🏼
It's a very chill and cozy area, with tasty tea and cake. Its in a very convenient place, being near many hotels and local stores

This place serves alcohol and has draft beer. Never would have know that by the name. A nice place to stop by if you want to have a drink. Our hotel is around the corner and this is a great option if you want a place to chill.

places.name: 一角鯨咖啡 Monodon Coffee

plus_code.compound_code: 3G49+7X 光能里 台灣台北市大同區

places.formatted_address: No. 10號, Lane 49, Chifeng St, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 103

reviews.text:
Good tasty coffee, excellent AC, free icy cold water provided, super clean restroom, superb service, even the sesame cake was so so delicious.  What else can you ask for after a long walk and simply need a place to rest and settle.

My nth time here and still enjoy this little cafe.
Excellent quality of matcha!! Probably one of the best I’ve tried in Taiwan! Cheesecake is very good too. And staff is very welcoming
Nice matcha latte & high mountain oolong tea
Super friendly staff, nice coffee and cakes ! Their dog is sooo cute too 😍

Comfortable atmosphere

PS: required min one drink per pax

reviews.text: It is a must-visit for coffee lovers and anyone looking to expand their palate. It’s rare to find a place that combines such a diverse range of high-quality coffee with a warm, inviting atmosphere. During my short stay in Taipei, I have already visited twice and I’m already looking forward to my next visit when I get to Taipei again.

A must-come if you’re a coffee lover! It was so good we came back twice during our stay. You know it’s good coffee when they ONLY sell coffee plus 1-2 bakes on the side. :)

We ordered an iced latte (dark roast) loved it with the milk foam and Kenya pourover (refreshing)! Highly highly recommended!

Super cute café with great drinks and snacks.

Went here with a friend and we both enjoyed the inside of the café, especially the two level layout. It was not too crowded and a great place to have a good chat.

The matcha and mochi tea latte drinks were very tasty. Out of the tiramisu and the American cheescake, we enjoyed the cheesecake the most :)

Can definitely recommend going here for a quick coffee or a chat. For working the tables (at least upstairs) are a bit too low to be comfortable.
A very small and cozy cafe. We ordered cranberry bagel and black tea canele. Canele was very special and filled with black tea taste. Medium roast hot latte was good too. Will visit again.

Great hospitality, sophisticated coffee and attention to detail can be seen in every aspect of the menu.
This is the perfect place to enjoy a heart-warming time.
Why not come and experience its charm for yourself?

places.name: Komeda‘s Coffee

reviews.text: Nice cafe.  Not really for dinner.  The beef bourguignon is thin and not cooked long enough.  Anthony Bourdain has a wonderfully recipe online.   It's not difficult it just takes time.   The service was excellent and the environment is pleasant. Breakfast is the best thing here!

I’m a tourist from UK, this is my first time been to Taipei, the desserts and coffee are amazing! Also, the staff who called Xixi is gorgeous and cute ,she served me very well, thanx to her and hope she can get promotion.
Best wishes!
Not as nice as in Japan Komeda. But it will cure my longing for now

Loved my experience here!
I got the iced Vienna coffee and simple lunch set. Everything was delicious, even the complimentary peanuts.
SUCH A BAD SERVICE! Coffees are not worthy of the money at all!

reviews.text: Opens early in morning. I got there just after 8.15am on a Sunday and there were already a number of customers sitting there already. They offer breakfast sets. Reasonable price. I paid TWD170 for a breakfast set including cup of black coffee, boiled egg and butter toast. Comfortable seating. Quite spacious. Popular

They have good coffee beans but coffee is not their main selling point so the good coffee that they have are usually just sit on the shelf.  Even the story employee says those good coffees only sold few of them in a week.
And the coffee bean that they use to serve coffee with are just normal average coffee which are not as good as the gourmet coffee that they have on the shelf.
Place is clean, food is simple but nicely prepared and taste great too.

i love coming here few times a week to get some solid breakfast before  my workout. Friendly to get some work done too, but no power outlet.
The sesame coffee is great! Be aware, really busy at weekend!

Usually packed, need to wait for the next available seat but difficult to because people usually stay there for long time. Been here for at least 3 times but left at the end because of wait.  Other than that,  it's pretty good overall.

reviews.text: This coffee shop is an absolute gem! The coffee is outstanding, and with variety of selections to suit every taste. The staff is incredibly friendly, attentive, and clearly passionate about what they do. Highly recommend this place for anyone looking for great pour over coffee and even better service!

I found the cafe from Google Maps, such a great experience! The atmosphere was really nice, also very nicely decorated. The owner and the barista are great too, they taught a lot about coffee and give me some brief introduction before I ordered. There are some fish tanks and a turtle in the cafe too! 🙌

Coffee brewing is a fine art in taiwan, and I was luckily invited by friends to witness the artisan transformation of a variety of single origin coffee beans to this liquid gold. Thanks Zackary, one the owners, for demonstrating your crafts and passions!

A new open café ,hot Yirgacheffe is good~but the serving process and training is 5% to 100% ~I'll pay your star back if you're ready!
11/26 update
raining day ,i need a cup of latte to comfort the cold heart....good....strong flavor , sweet lady ,nice caffee...well ,pay your star back.....and i will be back ...

Quaint and relaxing coffee roastery in a relaxing neighbourhood. The owner is very down to earth and is knowledgeable about his roasts. Amazing variety of beans and they have some food as well. Fantastic service was provided as well. The menu is seasonal as the bean rotation changes ever so often. Would recommend this place to anyone looking for a short break during the day! (Ask for the english menu if you have difficulty reading the menu)

An amazing Bakery with delicious cakes, pastries, and Bread

places.name: 好啊咖啡（五六營業至23:30）

places.formatted_address: No. 46號, Wanquan St, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10354

reviews.text:
Passed this a few times on the way home from work always looked busy.

It’s a nice place the seating is a bit uncomfortable, was trying to work with my computer the table was a bit small, was told could only sit in a two seat table which I suppose is fair if it’s only me.

But wasn’t busy at the time so would have like a bit more space to work.

I had a coffee was really good actually nice and hot, and a cookie, very small bought two.

There is a cat going around the coffee shop, cute but can be annoying and everyone is chasing it around and taking photos.

Overall it’s ok, not a place I’d return to.

One really cool thing is all the Christmas decorations, as a foreigner in Taiwan many years it’s lovely to have a Christmas feeling.

Very nice place to have chitchatting with friends, working or just space out a bit. Coffee was okay, atmosphere was really great. Clean environment is a big point. They also offered wifi, a bit pity that just cash payment only.

Great cafe in the heart of Zhongshan area serving up a variety of matcha desserts and drinks.

They have QR code menus at each table, but the website doesn’t update whether or not things are sold out throughout the day; the staff will do their best to notify you in a timely fashion.

During my first visit, I got the Early Grey Latte ($160 NT) and a Matcha Crepe Cake with matcha ice cream and matcha syrup ($280 NT). A little on the pricier side but well worth it and everything was delicious. During my second visit, we tried the Thai Tea (in a bear glass, $160 NT), Matcha Latte ($220 NT), Matcha Crepe Cake with matcha syrup and a side of fresh mangos ($240 NT), and lemon and earl grey madelines ($38 NT each).

They usually have seats available during the weekdays and you can walk in. If you decide to come on the weekend, make sure to reserve in advance or be prepared to wait.

The weekend late night cafe I found out of boredom.
Really made me feel comfortable place 👍🏻
Green tea dessert and drink all so much good.
Highly recommended!!
It is a lovely shop with delicious food and desserts, but without reservation, sometimes you need patience to wait.

I hope you will improve all of your food as me and my friend spent so much money there
Cute small coffee shop that offers healthy fare and desserts. I had the apple pie and the iced coffee and both were excellent. The experience overall with the food and the ambience was great!

This café does deserve its almost perfect score!

Cool and chillin place worth spending an afternoon with friends or yourself alone. I like the gourmet coffee with good quality and rich taste here, as well as delicious baguettes and fusion meals (can’t miss its south-asian-styled curry & braised beef)

Young and friendly are the bosses, the female one of whom seems interested in  handcrafts, so here are also many exquisite women's accessories, nice-looking mugs, wine, and coffee beans sold

Probably the worst iced black and curry chicken “sandwich” I’ve ever had in my life. I may have mistaken the Chinese description on the 三明治 and I’m willing to be corrected
The red peppercorns sprinkled on the “curry” is really disgusting
This is a beautiful and cozy coffee shop. I had a floral smell single origin coffee and enjoyed its fruity taste. It is worth to visit again and try another one.

places.name: UNI Cafe

reviews.text: Vibey cafe where the cats are the main highlight ✨ the owner is so kind, and so good to the two cats in store. I had an iced americano, which was okay, but I loved the slow atmosphere and cute cats walking around

Cute cafe with a couple cats and a sweet old man owner in Shida area! The angry looking cat is my fav and they don’t mind being pet. The WiFi is fine and there’s usually enough seating, although the seats are small and sometimes can be uncomfortable. There aren’t plugs however. The tea is good, the matcha latte is too much milk and not enough matcha. The desserts are tasty, including the biscuit and cookies. The old man is very sweet!

Great place to study and work or just hang out with some grumpy cats.

The handmade coffee here is amazing. The owner let me smell them all before selecting the flavor I wanted. I also appreciated the decor and tables. The cats themselves are super cute and not shy towards people. All came up to investigate me and my stuff. I will definitely come back here because I love cats and the vibe here is just great for reading a book.
We took the americano coffee to go. It was so bad that we drank a few sips and had to throw it away. Waste of money
Great！👍

places.name: Fika Fika Cafe

places.formatted_address: No. 33號, Yitong St, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 104

reviews.text: Love this cafe. Very bright and warm cafe with pleasant service. You can get around easily in English, the menus has extensive food and drink options. I got tea and a latte during my two visits, but lots of great coffee brewed here. While I did not get lunch or breakfast, the Lemon Cake wasexcellent. There is plenty of different seating options from small tables, to long tables, to desk setups. This is a decent place to work as well with Wifi and power sockets (sockets mostly in the back area that looks like two levels of bars.

We stopped by since we were in the area. It was full. High-quality coffee, great staff, nice location by a park. Some people work there even though there's supposedly 2 hr limit. Chatted with one cute female staff in English. She was friendly.
Desserts were 5 stars! The cinnamon roll was excellent! 4 stars for the drinks. Very friendly environment, would recommend!

very friendly staff and lovely cafe! This has been my go-to during my trip in taipei since this place opens consistently and early enough in the morning.

I also bought some beans home to enjoy. 😊

Their coffee is so good! It makes sense why they're ranked no. 3 in Taipei. I got the ham and cheese croissant along with an ice latte with oatmilk. This was such a delicious breakfast! You bet I bought a bag of coffee beans and a box of grounds in the sachets.

places.name: Yellow Monday Coffee & Croffle｜現烤可頌鬆餅、精品咖啡、外送下午茶

plus_code.compound_code: 3H53+6W 東昌里 台灣台北市松山區

places.formatted_address: No. 124號, Section 4, Minsheng E Rd, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 105

reviews.text:
Passing by during the typhoon day, it was raining heavily outside. When I first into the store, the smell of the croffle hits me hard that I gotta orders one.

Tried their latte with almond milk ( I usually have oat latte but because of the voucher I got gotta choose the oat milk one) it was good but I was expecting the coffee flavor could be a bit stronger. Maybe I’ll add another shot next time.

As a huge matcha fan, I ordered the matcha croffle. Gotta say that it’s relatively huge compared to the other croffle store I’ve eaten in Taipei. Price wise was pretty reasonable. The croffle was so crispy ( it’s not mochi-like texture ones but I love their crispy tastes)

Owner and staff was kind and nice. Seeing their store vision and color “yellow,” suddenly can brighten your day. It’s a nice “ shelter” place when you feel low or just want to hide from the reality, or hiding from the rain.

Will be back try different flavor croffles :)

Bumped in this cute café attracted by the branding and the mesmerising croffles (croissants toasted in a waffle machine). And so glad I did. I’ve chosen an iced Osmanthus latte and a Matcha croffle at start. Ended up getting 2 more croffles. The owner Pei, is really kind and nice to talk to. Totally recommend. So bad there aren’t any places like these in London.

It’s a good place for a cup of coffee and waffles! They are highly efficient and I barely needed to wait after I ordered osmanthus latte. ( I think this might be one of the most popular flavored latte because many people ordered this one. Lol )
Their coffee is good and price is reasonable!I saw many people visited this coffee shop and had their coffee to go. 😉
I will definitely visit this coffee shop in the near future.

Cute small shop that sells pretty good croffles.
Your day will definitely get better after you come here because they serve with a big warm smile.

One word: croffle.
Wow. The crunch and crisp of a waffle with the buttery layered inside. On top is a bit of melted brown sugar and sugar powder. A delightful snack to enjoy.

I came for a pick-me-up coffee but stayed for the croffle. Turned the Monday blues to a Yellow Monday.

places.name: OTOME Café 南海店

reviews.text: Coffee is very good yet very affordable. The shop itself is aesthetic with minimalistic theme. I order the sea salt coffee which tasted really good.
Very tasty coffee, very friendly staff and service
Came here without expectation but .... i found one of my favorite Uji Matcha.
Nice coffee shop 😁

訂外送美式咖啡+牛肉起司潛艇堡組合
美式選中培另外加了冰淇淋，咖啡喝起來很水很淡，沒有咖啡香（有點像是按到洗機器沖出來的咖啡水）加了冰淇淋，正常來說喝起來口感會很滑順，卻感覺有加跟沒加冰淇淋沒什麼差別，牛肉潛艇堡吃起來中規中矩，不過生菜水分可能甩的不夠乾，麵包體偏濕，影響口感，包裝上有感覺店家很用心經營

reviews.text:
Went here based on reviews. Ordered a coffee and Panini. Coffee was good. Paining horrible- barely any chicken used and the bread was the crust at the end so it was super dry and hard.
They offer a free coffee upgrade for a 5 star review on Google. Hence all the 5 star reviews.

Avocado Coffee is heaven! I came across this cafe as i’m looking for a unique coffee experience in Taipei and this place didn’t disappoint. The place is also surrounded by beautiful local boutiques so you can go for shopping immediately after your coffee run.
Staffs are friendly, atmosphere is cozy and calm . Stayed for an hour and had 2 coffee.

I also tried watermelon coffee. It was definitely a must try too!

Highly recommended! 😍

Great cafe. Modern stylish, minimalistic design. Signature coffee tasted great - even crazy flavors like Watermelon Iced coffee. The vanilla pudding was delicious too.
Apple pay accepted here!

For coffee lovers, this place offers oat milk, macadamia milk and a few variations. They also serve cold brews.

There is also a downstairs space where it’s quieter if the upstairs is packed.

Food wise, although very limited - try the danish butter toast!

Great little neighborhood coffee shop. Small upstairs but offers downstairs seating which is quite expansive and larger than expected. Calm atmosphere with background music and industrial design theme. Coffee is good. Takes time to make but worth slowing things down to enjoy. Can recommend. Good options and snacks like scones and waffles are also available.
