reviews.text:
Small place with decent food options especially when a lot of cafes tend to open later, this is a good option for early birds!
The cafe adopts a clean n bright concept basic but functional :)
The croissant came in fancy presentation .. A for effort !

Of all the specialty coffee shops I've been to in the area, this one wins for quality and service while being one of the best priced. It's cute and clean, but not trying too hard to be cool. And they serve delicious croissants by local Taipei bakery MyCroissant by Guillaume.

Excellent expresso, crema is perfect, tasty.
Also perfect Americano (many places make it as a tea).

Food has good flavors but you don’t get much for the price (very thin piece of salmon in the salmon sandwich).

It can also a take a while, but cafe has a nice atmosphere to sit and wait. Overall, decent average cafe.

This little place is great. The service is great, just remember it is not a chain store so everything is made after you order it. He has specialty coffees in addition to regular espresso, americano, etc. atmosphere is relaxed and food is good.

places.name: Lavazza Cafe

plus_code.compound_code: 2GRX+99 仁愛里 台灣台北市大安區

places.formatted_address: 106, Taiwan, Taipei City, Da’an District, 敦化南路1段228號2樓

reviews.text: Plenty of seating. Located on 1st floor. Reasonable prices. Coffee. Cakes. Spaghetti. Indoor seating and seating on the balcony outside. Min spend TWD200 per person. Good for chatting with friends. Opens until late
A quiet coffee shop on the first floor. It's so lovely to catch up with  family/friends. The cake was tasty with Lavazza coffee. It's much better than the large famous coffee shop right next door.

The classic Taipei old cafe, they have tasty hot chocolate and the puff pastry on the sea cream soup. The best part here is all the waiters and waitresses are friendly and their smiles are super warm!!

When people go to Lavazza.. the main reason is to get good Italian Lavazza coffe.. i am ok with the minimum 200 NTD.. but don’t force me to eat or buy not good food to reach the 200!! Take the 200 and give me my 130 or 190 coffee i am ok.. why you insist that i buy food !!
And weird music you are playing!! Many App would have cheerful Italian music (or even use local music) why you play weird French music ? If you represent Lavazza you should know the type of customers who will come to you really

All food and beverage was sub par. The lasagna was alright but couldn't really taste the ricotta cheese. The chicken was quite juicy though. I would recommend getting this instead.

I completely lost my appetite when the water cup still had lip stick stain from a previous customer. The utensil were not clean. It is clear that they are not too serious about hygiene.

They brought out the cake way before our meal. We asked for them to bring it back which the server refused at first stating they don't have any room....(umm hello? didn't it come from your fridge?)

The latte was alright but I personally didn't like the milk foam. It seems like it was made from a 711 coffee machine.

places.name: BOBBY & FRIENDS. CAFE 巴比咖啡

plus_code.compound_code: 3G39+8P 光能里 台灣台北市大同區

places.formatted_address: No. 53號, Nanjing W Rd, Datong District, Taipei City, Taiwan 103

reviews.text: I really liked the mac&cheese sandwich! Also the chili dog was good. Pretty good, but the matcha was way too sweet and coffee was just okay.

I had a Sicily lemon americano and a tuna sandwich. Both were really delicious and good value for money - the sandwich was larger than I expected at that price point.

The place is small but cozy enough - also for dining in.

The staff was accommodating and friendly.

Great place to pick up a coffee to go or for taking a small rest while you plan your day in Taipei!
Quite a small area with not much seats available for dining in. Sandwiches and lattes are delicious.

Love the vibe and coffee here. Ordered an iced americano, it has "modern" taste with balance of fruitiness and sweetness. The milk tea my partner ordered is average though.
Seats arrangement are optimized for quick drink or bite, not a full meal.

This cafe has a great atmosphere, a great place to spend time alone pr with 1 friend. the seat is a bit weird but nevertheless still comfortable and nice.
Best healthy also delicious food I have ever eaten.
Coffee was also superb.
Will go here again for food and coffee.

places.name: COFFEE.TEA.OR - 敦南概念店 ｜手搖飲料店｜咖啡專門店

reviews.text: To be honest, I only went here because I'm a fan of Ben Wu's and he co-owns the shop. I didn't meet him but it turns out that this is a pretty good place to study or relax/read while enjoying a drink. There's usually a steady stream of people on the side that sells glasses so it's not too quiet, and while there are only a couple of tables in the front, they usually seem to be open. The baristas generally don't seem very nice or helpful, but they also aren't rude. I've only ever tried the 鮮肉蜜柚 (grapefruit oolong tea which I like a lot) and the 小芋圓奶茶 (taro balls milk tea). I would recommend against getting full sugar though! I always reduce sugar anyway but my friend got a bubble milk tea with full sugar... the bubbles were fine but it was almost undrinkable with how sweet it was (even for her, and she likes sweet drinks).

The room was bright and is shared with an eyeglasses store. The tea was refreshing, didn't try the coffee. The best part was the stable and fast WiFi. I was here in the evening and it was fairly quiet. Just a few people in the eyeglasses area and a couple having a coffee.
Very good coffee and incredible service, I highly recommend
Good to drink! Fashion glasses store!
good tea

places.formatted_address: No. 28-8號, Jinzhou St, Zhongshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 10491

reviews.text: Taste good. If you're looking for frash beverage, you sould go to this place!!!

Best coffee place in town.  Daily visits since the day of opening 10 years ago. Very good coffee, lovely and friendly personnel, Owners are top of the top and hope it will stay open for many years to come
Drinks and cakes are fantastic.
GOOD
Tastes Good

places.formatted_address: No. 23號, Alley 6, Lane 136, Section 4, Roosevelt Rd, Zhongzheng District, Taipei City, Taiwan 100

reviews.text:
Quite place in the small alley, located right around the crowded Gong-guan area. Perfect hidden gem where to enjoy chitchat with friends or just relax. Limited seat environment with Korean vibe decorations.

Matcha latte was okay, can make the sugar-free drink as you requested. Will try the dessert if there’s any 2nd visit opportunity.
Love Potion 1204, very cozy celebration for Seokjin . Looking forward to ALB’s exhibition in Taipei!

Quiet space, good quality products and cozy atmosphere.

This cute café is quite hidden in a busy neighborhood, but embraces the quietness in return. There are only a few seats available but it’s also not too crowded on weekday afternoon. Free wifi here and the tables are big enough. No time limit on weekdays. I’d recommend anyone who is searching for a place to study or work during weekdays.

Food is nice. We ordered a slice of lemon cake and a big cookie. The cookie is filled with melted chocolate, which is what I’d call the comfort food. As for the drink, the Scottish black tea is fused with butter and light spices. It’s worth a try. I regret not taking the butter toast. The house smelled like a freshly baked bread when someone ordered the toast. I’d definitely go back and try this one!

It’s definitely a go to place around NTU campus if you’re searching for a corner to read/study.

It's hidden at the end of the alley,  small but quiet and taste good Latte.
Worth to have a break here.

Comfortable coffee shop with nice music playlist.
Reasonable price.

Ps. If Google maps suggests you to walk to this shop from the power building, don't follow it. Take a walk from the night market. From the power building to the shop locate local people's houses and the road is not comfortable for walking.

places.name: 客美多咖啡 Komeda's Coffee 敦南信義店

reviews.text: The coffee is their signature and tastes amazing—I especially love the Viennese coffee. The seating is comfortable, and there’s no time limit, making it a perfect spot to work for an entire afternoon.

Passing by this restaurant for so many times, I finally went in for the first time! What a surprising experience! The servers we’re all very prompt and courteous. The contemporary Japanese dishes were delicious and pleasant to enjoy! Will come again very soon 🔜. Highly recommended!
Nice n cozy environment. I always love Komeda as they are always friendly n provide good coffee n food.

A typical Japanese Cafe chain restaurant. The meat sauce spaghetti tastes delicious. The meat sauce is a mix of pork and beef. The bread is soft and tasty. It’s a good restaurant for simple meal with coffee.
The fried pumpkin cookies were really yummy and the salad dressing was amazing. The vibe in the restaurant was also really good, I really enjoyed it.

reviews.text:
Wow, this carrot cake is amazing and perfect for fall! Seriously, you will not be disappointed.
The brie open face sandwich is also good and has a nice savory, salty and crunchy flavor and the service was great, I'll definitely be back
My first coffee back in Taipei after riding around beautiful Taiwan. And it’s absolutely delicious!!

Great, chic coffee shop for working or catching up with friends. The interior design of the first floor is optimized for space and light while the second floor is a bit cramped and dark. Great variety of drinks and friendly baristas who can explain the menu and options in detail.

Kind of a cute neighborhood cafe, corner location means lots of natural lighting, light colored decor=calm and comfort.  Gentle, soft music, quiet and peaceful! Single origin and latte both were excellent, good quality!  Of course, the large fish tank with seatings around really adds personality.
A nice coffee and a great sandwich in a very well designed cafe. I really enjoy the window seating where it’s great to sit on a pleasant day and relax with a coffee.

reviews.text:
Unique and attractive cafe. We were drawn by their extraordinary flavored selections of three musician brands of coffee - Bach, Beethoven, and Mozart. It’s a busy cafe. Be Prepared to wait long when it’s a peak hour. We waited for 40 minutes on our last visit. We could understand since some customers just ordered a few dozen of drip coffee. You can imagine when the coffee is dripping to fill the cup… 🤣
But the servers are friendly and sweet.
Last day in Taiwan and got to try really good coffee and breakfast!!

A very relax and comfortable cafe that you could have your special coffee, fruit tea and dessert!!!
Love that berry fresh fruits tea, so “fruitful”. Coffee ice-ball with hot milk pouring in is also a correct choice!
Spent few hours here waiting someone is such a good decision. No one will kick you out even you finish your drink and dessert. The staff is so friendly and professional in introducing the menu.
The have basement too for guests to book and having small meeting here, projector could be provided. What an amazing service, good for local company!!!
Awesome coffee, amazing service, nice atmosphere.

Interesting cafe with some cool concepts, the food was nice, combo was interesting, unexpected but tasty. The coffee ice ball was a treat, unlike anything I’d seen before. Worth a stop if you’re in the neighbourhood.

places.name: CURISTA COFFEE Taipei City Hall Shop

plus_code.compound_code: 2HR7+JM 新仁里 台灣台北市信義區

places.formatted_address: 110, Taiwan, Taipei City, Xinyi District, Section 4, Zhongxiao E Rd, 563號1樓

reviews.text:
A really really great and quaint little place. Happened on it by chance but really fell in love with this place! The atmosphere is wonderful, really love the design~ a bit more on the modern side :)

The people were amazing! Really sweet and really helpful! We tried their Americano and Pourover coffee, both of which were really nice! Had their cheese pizza, which was good but a bit on the small side (not bad for us since we just wanted a snack).

Seating is spacious and they provide little baskets for baggies. Great place all in all and would definitely go back!

The coffee, latte, and the cake are so delicious. The shop is so clean and the team members are so professional to make each cup of the coffee. Highly recommend to anyone looking for high quality coffee.

This place looks so modern and cool and I’m happy I dropped in for a visit. It has a very open concept and there is plenty of seating with natural light. There is an island in the middle of the room where all the drinks are made and food prepared. There is a good variety of teas, coffees, and juices to suit most people and an assortment of baked goods(croissants)and snacks to satisfy a sweet tooth. The decor and seating layout is modern looking with a unique twist on everything you’d expect to see in a coffee shop. We got a matcha latte and a cold Americano. The matcha latte was good and the coffee had a fresh fruity flavor as many shops offer now. I was happy with the service (English) and the professional attitude of the staff. I’d definitely go there again if I’m in the neighborhood.

This cafe has great coffee and a cool vibe! It’s pretty big and has a bunch of locations around Taipei, but this one’s near MRT City Hall.

It’s the kind of place you can chill for a bit with your drink. They do have charging spots, but honestly, most people aren’t working here since the seats aren’t super comfy for that. It’s better for hanging out and chatting.

Prices aren’t bad, and their cake is really good too!
Stylish coffee shop with a broad range of coffees available. Knowledgeable and friendly staff. Had an excellent cup of pour over Panamanian coffee - light roasted.

reviews.text: Busy place on a weekend afternoon. Everyone has to order at least one drink. Large choices of drinks available. Second floor, access via a not so obvious staircase.

Coffee and  meals are so delicious!
waffle is so rich of fruits and. Ice cream!
It’s Popular  coffee shop in Taipei

Food and beverages are decently delicious. Haha decently~ given its a hyped cafe. It's a friend who wanted to go... One thing I noted to all who eat-in, minimally to order one drink / pax (exclusive of food order despite you order more than one share / pax). And they are inflexible on this rule.

Went to this place before which was great. But I think they now have a new policy where your minimum order must include a drink, you can't just order a pancake or waffles or dessert or a main meal, you have to order a drink even if you order any of the above. It's quite a strange policy, I'm sure there is a reason for it, it's my first time seeing a restaurant with this policy. Not here to complain, but just informing other guests that this policy exists. It was unfortunate, because at the end we didn't have a chance to taste their food.

Love this place!! Food were delicious & didn't fail to impress on presentation & flavours. Staffs were very helpful & attentive.
Not sure if it is part of company's way of operating, but there were no staff uniform worn. Staffs were dressed in their own styles making it seemed a very homely & casual place to work in. 👍🏼
Only downside is that each of us had to order a drink even though we had already ordered a main course each.

places.name: Nanjing23 Cafe (Nanjing Ershen Coffee)

plus_code.compound_code: 3H25+W6 東光里 台灣台北市松山區

places.formatted_address: No. 1-5號, Alley 6, Lane 23, Section 5, Nanjing E Rd, Songshan District, Taipei City, Taiwan 105

reviews.text:
Small, tidy cafe space with table and window seating. Offers house made dacquoise and cinnamon rolls.

House latte blend was a darker roast that edged bitter. They offer oat milk (oatly) and teas.

Dacquoise are refrigerated, so I waited to let it reach room temp before trying. It has a slightly cakier chew, so I think it was refrigerated a while for the filling to moisten the shells.

Would like to try more of their fruit and tea drinks.

** Since JAN 2022, the plot across the street is demolished and has been under heavy construction. I think once the windows and doors are closed, the noise is diminished, but still audible over the music.

3.5 - Would return, particularly to work.
Matcha needs a no sugar, ceremony-grade version, or stick to just coffee. Cute spot, might try again.

This is my favorite neighborhood coffee spot!

The owner is a super chill, very friendly nice guy (I’ve seen him deliver cups of coffee around the community for his regulars). The drinks are tasty and quality is pretty good for the price you pay.

My partner often enjoys the oat milk latte with a deep roast; I like getting the matcha lattes with oat milk or the honey cinnamon latte with oat milk. He also has a nice collection of non caffeinated drinks!

While the cafe is quite cozy, there’s more seating than you’d think, and the atmosphere is pretty comfortable and brightly lit with natural light.

Everything at Nanjing23 is top notch and fairly priced. The service is friendly, the boss and his assistants are always on point, and the atmosphere is a nice neighborhood vibe. Nice for having a drink there or take out, but do note it gets crowded around lunchtime so it may be hard to find a seat.

The regular coffees and lattes are made well,  but you should also try the hand-ground matcha  latte, the honey cinnamon latte, and their range of seasonal drinks (the summertime drinks are 😙👌)
The service is as nice as the food and the drinks. I really recommend this place. It is a small coffee place where we feel at home. 謝謝 😊
